{"format": "tiptap/v1", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why Not Just Use BERT's [CLS] Token?"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "BERT's "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "[CLS]"}, {"type": "text", "text": " vector was trained for next-sentence prediction, not semantic similarity. Comparing two sentences with it requires passing both together as a pair — which is "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "O(n²)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for a corpus of "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "n"}, {"type": "text", "text": " sentences. For 10 000 sentences that's 50 million BERT forward passes — completely infeasible for search."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Sentence-BERT (Reimers & Gurevych, 2019) fine-tunes BERT with a siamese network so each sentence is encoded independently into a fixed-size vector. Similarity is then a single cosine dot product — "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "O(1) per pair"}, {"type": "text", "text": " once embeddings are pre-computed. A full 10 000-sentence comparison that would take 65 hours with vanilla BERT takes 5 seconds with Sentence-BERT."}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Siamese network: Sentence A and B each pass through a shared-weight BERT encoder + mean pooling to produce vectors u and v. Cosine similarity between u and v is compared to a gold similarity score via MSE loss. Use cases shown at the bottom: semantic similarity, search, clustering, duplicate detection."}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Training Objectives"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Sentence-BERT can be trained with three loss functions depending on the available data:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Regression (STS-B style)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": gold cosine scores 0–1 → MSE loss between predicted and gold."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Classification (NLI style)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": concatenate "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "[u, v, |u−v|]"}, {"type": "text", "text": " → softmax over entailment/neutral/contradiction → cross-entropy loss."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Triplet loss"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": anchor "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "a"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", positive "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "p"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", negative "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "n"}, {"type": "text", "text": " → minimise "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "max(0, cos(a,n) − cos(a,p) + margin)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ". Best for retrieval tasks with labelled triplets."}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Quick Start"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# pip install sentence-transformers\nfrom sentence_transformers import SentenceTransformer\nimport numpy as np\n\n# all-MiniLM-L6-v2: 80 MB, 384-dim, fast and strong\nmodel = SentenceTransformer(\"all-MiniLM-L6-v2\")\n\nsentences = [\n    \"A dog runs in the park.\",\n    \"A puppy plays outside.\",\n    \"The stock market crashed today.\",\n    \"Investors lost billions on Wall Street.\",\n]\n\nembeddings = model.encode(sentences, normalize_embeddings=True)\n# shape: (4, 384)  — already L2-normalised so dot product = cosine sim\n\n# Pairwise similarities\nsim = embeddings @ embeddings.T\nprint(sim.round(2))\n# [[1.   0.84 0.08 0.09]\n#  [0.84 1.   0.06 0.07]\n#  [0.08 0.06 1.   0.81]\n#  [0.09 0.07 0.81 1.  ]]\n# Dog sentences cluster together; finance sentences cluster together"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Semantic Search"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The canonical use-case: encode a corpus once, then find the closest passage to any query in milliseconds."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from sentence_transformers import SentenceTransformer, util\n\nmodel = SentenceTransformer(\"all-MiniLM-L6-v2\")\n\n# Offline step: encode corpus\ncorpus = [\n    \"Paris is the capital of France.\",\n    \"The Eiffel Tower stands in Paris.\",\n    \"Python is a popular programming language.\",\n    \"Machine learning is a subfield of AI.\",\n    \"The Seine river flows through Paris.\",\n]\ncorpus_embeddings = model.encode(corpus, convert_to_tensor=True,\n                                  normalize_embeddings=True)\n\n# Online step: encode query and retrieve\nquery = \"What is the capital city of France?\"\nquery_embedding = model.encode(query, convert_to_tensor=True,\n                                normalize_embeddings=True)\n\nhits = util.semantic_search(query_embedding, corpus_embeddings, top_k=3)[0]\nfor hit in hits:\n    print(f\"{hit['score']:.3f}  {corpus[hit['corpus_id']]}\")\n# 0.892  Paris is the capital of France.\n# 0.731  The Eiffel Tower stands in Paris.\n# 0.698  The Seine river flows through Paris."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Choosing a Model"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Model"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dim"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Size"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Best for"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "all-MiniLM-L6-v2"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "384"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "80 MB"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fast search, CPU-friendly, general English"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "all-mpnet-base-v2"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "768"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "420 MB"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Highest quality general-purpose"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "multi-qa-mpnet-base-dot-v1"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "768"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "420 MB"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Q&A retrieval (asymmetric search)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "paraphrase-multilingual-MiniLM-L12-v2"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "384"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "470 MB"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "50+ languages"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fine-Tuning on Your Own Data"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from sentence_transformers import SentenceTransformer, InputExample, losses\nfrom torch.utils.data import DataLoader\n\nmodel = SentenceTransformer(\"all-MiniLM-L6-v2\")\n\n# Training pairs: (sentence_a, sentence_b, gold_score 0.0-1.0)\ntrain_examples = [\n    InputExample(texts=[\"A dog runs.\", \"A puppy plays.\"], label=0.85),\n    InputExample(texts=[\"I love Python.\", \"Python is great.\"], label=0.92),\n    InputExample(texts=[\"The sky is blue.\", \"I like pizza.\"], label=0.05),\n]\n\ntrain_dataloader = DataLoader(train_examples, shuffle=True, batch_size=16)\ntrain_loss = losses.CosineSimilarityLoss(model)\n\n# Fine-tune for 1 epoch\nmodel.fit(\n    train_objectives=[(train_dataloader, train_loss)],\n    epochs=1,\n    warmup_steps=10,\n    output_path=\"my-fine-tuned-model\",\n)\n\n# Reload and use\nmodel = SentenceTransformer(\"my-fine-tuned-model\")"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Scaling with FAISS"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For millions of passages, a linear scan over all embeddings is too slow. FAISS (Facebook AI Similarity Search) builds an approximate nearest-neighbour index that answers queries in sub-millisecond time:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# pip install faiss-cpu\nimport faiss\nimport numpy as np\nfrom sentence_transformers import SentenceTransformer\n\nmodel = SentenceTransformer(\"all-MiniLM-L6-v2\")\n\ncorpus = [\"doc_\" + str(i) for i in range(100_000)]  # placeholder\nembeddings = model.encode(corpus, normalize_embeddings=True,\n                           show_progress_bar=True, batch_size=512)\nembeddings = np.array(embeddings, dtype=np.float32)\n\n# Build a flat L2 index (exact search; swap for IndexIVFFlat for ANN)\ndim   = embeddings.shape[1]   # 384\nindex = faiss.IndexFlatIP(dim)  # inner product = cosine for normalised vecs\nindex.add(embeddings)\n\nquery_vec = model.encode([\"my search query\"], normalize_embeddings=True)\nD, I = index.search(np.array(query_vec, dtype=np.float32), k=5)\nprint(I)   # indices of top-5 most similar docs\nprint(D)   # cosine similarity scores"}]}]}}